---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
---
<ProjectLayout
  title="Lead Scoring System"
  description="Lead Scoring System - AI-assisted development of an XGBoost ML model delivering $1.4M+ annual ROI through intelligent lead filtering."
>
    <section class="project-hero">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="status-badge">Active Development</div>
            <h1 class="project-title">Lead Scoring System</h1>
            <p class="project-lead">Using Claude Code, I developed a machine learning solution that identifies which leads to filter, delivering $1.4M+ guaranteed annual ROI through operational efficiency.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="project-section--alt">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>The Challenge</h2>
            <p>In my role at an EdTech company, I identified a critical inefficiency: our sales team processed hundreds of thousands of annual leads with an enrollment rate of less than 3%. This meant massive effort spent on leads unlikely to convert.</p>
            <p class="mt-1">Rather than traditional lead prioritization, I asked a different question: <strong>What if we could confidently identify which leads NOT to pursue?</strong></p>

            <h3 class="subsection-title--lg">The Impact</h3>
            <div class="card-grid--sm">
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-card__value">23%</div>
                    <div class="stat-card__label">of leads safely filtered</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-card__value">$1.4M+</div>
                    <div class="stat-card__label">annual operational savings</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-card__value">95%+</div>
                    <div class="stat-card__label">confidence in filtering decisions</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-card__value">3.5%</div>
                    <div class="stat-card__label">true miss rate after recovery</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="project-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Development with Claude Code</h2>
            <p>As a CX Manager without formal data science training, I used Claude Code to build this solution. My domain expertise guided the development while Claude Code handled the technical implementation.</p>

            <h3 class="subsection-title mt-2">The Evolution</h3>
            <div class="card-grid mt-2">
                <div class="phase-card">
                    <h4>Phase 1: Baseline</h4>
                    <div class="phase-card__subtitle">Simple logistic regression model</div>
                    <div class="phase-card__status"><strong>Performance:</strong> 57.7% accuracy</div>
                    <p class="mt-1" style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-text-light);">Proved the concept but needed improvement</p>
                </div>
                <div class="phase-card">
                    <h4>Phase 2: Enhanced</h4>
                    <div class="phase-card__subtitle">XGBoost with richer features</div>
                    <div class="phase-card__status"><strong>Performance:</strong> 75.8% accuracy (+31%)</div>
                    <p class="mt-1" style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-text-light);">Added temporal patterns and behavioral signals</p>
                </div>
                <div class="phase-card--active">
                    <h4>Phase 3: Production-Ready ‚≠ê</h4>
                    <div class="phase-card__subtitle">Refined and calibrated</div>
                    <div class="phase-card__status"><strong>Status:</strong> Deployment-ready</div>
                    <p class="mt-1" style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-text-light);">Optimized for business decisions with risk controls</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="project-section--alt">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>The "Don't Engage" Innovation</h2>
            <p>The breakthrough was reframing the problem. Instead of prioritizing leads, we identify the <strong>low-probability leads to safely ignore</strong>.</p>

            <div class="content-box">
                <h4>How It Works</h4>
                <p>The XGBoost model analyzes lead characteristics like enrollment intent, timing preferences, marketing channel, and engagement patterns to predict conversion probability. Leads scoring below a carefully calibrated threshold are filtered from sales outreach.</p>
                <div class="highlight-box--alt mt-1">
                    <strong>Risk Management:</strong> We set conservative thresholds (95%+ precision) and validated that 25% of "missed" enrollments happen through other channels anyway, reducing true risk to just 3.5%.
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3 class="subsection-title--lg">Business Value</h3>
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <ul class="styled-list">
                    <li><strong>Conservative Scenario:</strong> $1.4M AUD/year from time savings alone</li>
                    <li><strong>Realistic Scenario:</strong> $2.0M - $2.5M AUD/year as sales focuses on quality leads</li>
                    <li><strong>Strong Performance:</strong> $4M+ AUD/year with improved conversion rates</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="project-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>My Role & Approach</h2>
            <p>This project showcases how domain experts can leverage AI assistance to build sophisticated solutions without traditional coding backgrounds.</p>

            <div class="mt-2">
                <h3 class="subsection-title">What I Brought:</h3>
                <ul class="styled-list">
                    <li>Deep understanding of the enrollment sales process and pain points</li>
                    <li>Business context for evaluating model decisions and risk tolerance</li>
                    <li>Iterative problem refinement and validation of outputs</li>
                    <li>Translation between business needs and technical requirements</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-2">
                <h3 class="subsection-title">What Claude Code Brought:</h3>
                <ul class="styled-list">
                    <li>Machine learning expertise (XGBoost implementation)</li>
                    <li>Data analysis and feature engineering guidance</li>
                    <li>Best practices for model validation and deployment</li>
                    <li>Code generation and technical documentation</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="tech-stack-box">
                <h4>Technologies Used</h4>
                <div class="tech-badges">
                    <span class="project-meta"><span>XGBoost</span></span>
                    <span class="project-meta"><span>Python</span></span>
                    <span class="project-meta"><span>scikit-learn</span></span>
                    <span class="project-meta"><span>pandas</span></span>
                    <span class="project-meta"><span>Jupyter Notebooks</span></span>
                    <span class="project-meta"><span>Claude Code</span></span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="project-section--alt">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Key Learnings</h2>
            <div class="content-box--light">
                <ul class="styled-list--spaced">
                    <li><strong>Domain expertise is irreplaceable:</strong> Claude Code provided technical execution, but business context drove the innovation (inverting from "which leads to prioritize" to "which to filter")</li>
                    <li><strong>Iteration is essential:</strong> Three major versions, each informed by validating results against real business outcomes</li>
                    <li><strong>Transparency builds trust:</strong> Being upfront about work-in-progress status and model limitations helped stakeholder buy-in</li>
                    <li><strong>Tools like Claude Code lower barriers:</strong> Complex ML solutions are accessible to non-engineers willing to learn and collaborate</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</ProjectLayout>
